// map[byte]V.keys() and map[K]byte.values() would need to hand back a
// compact []byte, but the runtime builds keys()/values() results as a
// boxed Value::List of Value::Int regardless of K/V (sigs.rs types the
// result List(k)/List(v); there is no typed repack), so a []byte-typed
// result slot would hold a boxed list underneath -- the same
// repack-impossible shape sum()/join() already reject on a bare []byte
// receiver. Both are checker errors now; iterate with a for loop
// instead (task-9 review, IMPORTANT 3; the typed repack is backlogged).
fn main() {
    m := map[byte]str{104: "a"}
    ks := m.keys()
    n := map[str]byte{"a": 104}
    vs := n.values()
    print(len(ks))
    print(len(vs))
}
